      "content": {
        "title": "Posterior Cruciate and Collateral Ligament Injuries — Core Principles",
        "definition": "Injuries to the PCL, MCL, LCL, and posterolateral corner causing varus, valgus, or posterior instability of the knee.",
        "summary": "PCL injuries often from dashboard injury. PLC injuries require anatomic reconstruction. Combined ligament injuries have higher stiffness risk."
      },
